ATHLETICS: Commends Flau'jae Johnson for her outstanding achievements in athletics,
academics, leadership, and community service at Louisiana State University
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Flau'jae Johnson for her accomplishments at Louisiana State University.
3 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Flau'jae Johnson for her outstanding
4 achievements in athletics, leadership, and community service at Louisiana State University;
5 and
6 WHEREAS, Flau'jae Johnson enrolled at Louisiana State University in 2022 as an
7 exceptional student-athlete and has since emerged as one of the most accomplished
8 collegiate athletes in the nation; and
9 WHEREAS, as a freshman member of the LSU women's basketball team, Flau'jae
10 played a vital role in leading the team to victory in the 2023 NCAA National Championship,
11 contributing significantly as a starter on a historic championship roster; and
12 WHEREAS, throughout her collegiate career, Flau'jae has earned numerous
13 individual honors, including Southeastern Conference Freshman of the Year, multiple
14 All-Southeastern Conference selections, and multiple All-American recognitions,
15 culminating in her selection to the prestigious John R. Wooden All-America Team; and
16 WHEREAS, Flau'jae has further distinguished herself by representing the United
17 States in international competition, earning a gold medal as a member of Team USA in the
18 FIBA Women's AmeriCup; and
19 WHEREAS, beyond her accomplishments on the court, Flau'jae has demonstrated
20 exemplary leadership and service, earning national recognition as the recipient of the Kay
