1 Yow Servant Leader Award, which honors student-athletes who exemplify compassion,
2 advocacy, and a commitment to community service; and
3 WHEREAS, Flau'jae's advocacy efforts, particularly in raising awareness for cancer
4 research and her engagement with youth and community initiatives, have made a meaningful
5 and lasting impact across Louisiana and beyond; and
6 WHEREAS, Flau'jae has excelled academically as a student in the LSU Honors
7 College, pursuing a degree in nursing while maintaining a 4.0 grade point average,
8 demonstrating discipline and commitment to academic excellence; and
9 WHEREAS, in addition to her achievements in athletics and academics, Flau'jae has
10 used her platform as both a nationally recognized athlete and recording artist to inspire
11 young people and promote positive community engagement; and
12 WHEREAS, Flau'jae has positioned herself as a leading figure in collegiate athletics
13 through name, image, and likeness opportunities while maintaining a strong commitment to
14 integrity, responsibility, and service; and
15 WHEREAS, Flau'jae Johnson is an outstanding student-athlete and community
16 servant who has brought great pride to Louisiana State University and the state of Louisiana,
17 and she is deserving of the highest recognition for her many achievements.
18 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
19 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Flau'jae Johnson for her outstanding
20 achievements in athletics, academics, leadership, and community service at Louisiana State
21 University and does hereby extend sincere wishes for continued success and happiness in
22 all of her endeavors.
